<Title>good mp3 player overall
<Date>Fri Dec 30 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>this mp3 is very nice, its my third in 2 years and is the best over all. i wanted rhapsody to go which works great with this player but i needed a firmwire update, i was quite nervous durring the update because it erases the entire hard drive and reprograms, so if anything went wrong i would have a heep of plastic. but i didnt and the rhapsody service works good with it.  pros- - nice set up on current playing track similar to ipod - battery life is quite good - the touch wheel is nice but a little over sensitive (use lock feature at top) -HAS AMAZING SOUND even with the cheap head phones included - gets great radio reception with the ability to save 32 radio frequences and you can title them all - gets very loud, you can turn it up all the way and not have to use the ear buds - dj feature keeps track of most and least played, plus has an album of the day feature -clock, planner, alarm clock and many other orginizational features  cons- -horrible manual not even joking there are 10 pages in english and it is about inserting your battery and turning your player on so figuring out things is a hassle -battery take about 2 or 3 hours to charge, you might want to get a spare - the case included with some purchases is plastic and hard and always freaks my out when i try to get my micro out of it - the usb cord is hard to detach i always feel like im gonna break it - there have been many reports of the head phone jack getting loose and comming out (but no such thing is occuring in mine)  but otherwise this is an extremly good player with great sound and great features, it has verry similar controls to an ipod (but many more features) plus it works with almost all to go services which is nice because my family pays 15 bucks a month on rhapsody and in the past week or so i have gotten over 300 or 400 songs! no more 99 cent deals.  
